·instead, Riselle Sng made a journal entry crediting the sum to the 88888 account in CONTAC on 30 September. There is no evidence whether she did this on her own initiative or not, though the strong supposition is that it was on the instructions of Leeson. Miss Sng gave evidence before me but was not questioned on this point. There were in evidence both the journal entry prepared by Miss Sng (debiting Bank and crediting the 88888 account) and an extract from the daily activity statement for the 88888 account

