 combining schedule 7 of the BFS statement of claim and appendix 3 of D&T closing
	      ); the discrediting of local management and those in Leeson’s product lines far greater; the funding mechanisms of BSL’s Settlements Department and supervision by BSL’s Treasury would have been in question; and both the reputational damage and the cost of the controls needed to satisfy the regulators would have been far greater.

